    <section id="sect-00001">
    <title>Infrared Spectroscopy</title>
    <para id="para-00001">All carbonyl-containing compounds have intense IR absorptions in the range 1650 to 1850 cm<sup>–1</sup>. As shown in <link target-id="table-00001"/> the exact position of the absorption provides information about the specific kind of carbonyl group. For comparison, the IR absorptions of aldehydes, ketones, and carboxylic acids are included in the table, along with values for carboxylic acid derivatives.</para>
