    <section id="sect-00003">
    <title>Nuclear Magnetic Resonance Spectroscopy</title>
    <para id="para-00005">Hydrogens on the carbon next to a carbonyl group are slightly deshielded and absorb near 2 <emphasis effect="italics">δ</emphasis> in the <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum, although the exact identity of the carbonyl group can’t be determined. <link target-id="fig-00001"/> shows the <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum of ethyl acetate.</para>
    <figure class="scaled-down" id="fig-00001">
