    <para id="para-00006">Although <sup>13</sup>C NMR is useful for determining the presence or absence of a carbonyl group in a molecule, the identity of the carbonyl group is difficult to determine. Aldehydes and ketones absorb near 200 <emphasis effect="italics">δ,</emphasis> while the carbonyl carbon atoms of various acid derivatives absorb in the range 160 to 180 <emphasis effect="italics">δ</emphasis> (<link target-id="table-00002"/>).</para>
